==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Magician
<hw>Ma*gi"cian</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>magicien</ets>. See <er>Magic</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One skilled in magic; one who practices the black art;
an enchanter; a necromancer; a sorcerer or sorceress; a
conjurer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An entertainer who produces seemingly magical
effects by clever illusions; most magicians admit that the craft is mere
illusion, rather than a true supernatural art.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>magic lantern</ent>⟦br⟧
